A striking computational fluid and wave-particle dynamic simulation tracking passive energy recycling across an external wingsuit arm panel. High-speed wind shear forces representing a 200 km/h dive velocity are depicted as bright orange particle streams screaming across an outer micro-grooved FEP mesh face. The intense friction causes the mesh to build a glowing static potential field, color-coded in a brilliant electric gold. The simulation shows this charge being directly siphoned down internal micro-fluidic tracks filled with high-conductivity liquid gallium alloy, scientific data visualization overlay, deep contrast, black background, 8k --ar 16:9
